----- stdout -----
Explain a valid Semantic Version as parsed by the spec.

Breaks apart the Semantic Version, into it's individual components.

All values are returned as strings, because the unsigned integer types are not necessarily bound by a numeric type that is parsable by common libraries.

It is worth noting, Semver 2.0.0 §11.4.1 & §11.4.2 pre-release & metadata dot separated values, cannot be negative numbers, since they cannot be represented with hyphens.

Reference: https://semver.org/#spec-item-11

Usage: sem-tool explain [OPTIONS] <SEMANTIC_VERSION>

Arguments:
  <SEMANTIC_VERSION>
          

Options:
      --mcp
          Run an MCP server over stdio that exposes this CLI's clap schema

      --mcp-http <ADDR>
          Run an MCP server over Streamable HTTP at ADDR (e.g. 127.0.0.1:8080)

      --export-skills <DIR>
          Generate Agent Skills (SKILL.md) from tools, resources, and prompts, then exit

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

